contribution pension administrative services additionally the company engages in buying and selling gold selling securities investment trusts handling commercial papers providing interest rate derivatives currency derivatives and other derivatives and selling insurance policies it also offers investment banking and custodial syndication bond administrative real estate finance acquisition finance and corporate restructuring and project and asset finance services and asset management and investment trust services as of december   company had  branches and  subbranches in japan and  relevant offices and  representative offices internationally the company was formerly known as mizuho corporate bank ltd and changed its name to mizuho bank ltd in july  the company was founded in  and is headquartered in tokyo japan mizuho bank ltd is a subsidiary of mizuho financial group inc detailed description otemachi tower otemachichiyodakutokyo  japanfounded in  employees phone     wwwmizuhobankcojp key executives for mizuho bank ltd mr koji fujiwara ceo president  representative director age  mr makoto umemiya executive md head of financial control  accounting group managing executive officer  director age  mr daisaku abe deputy president head of operations group head of it  systems group  executive officer age  mr koji arita managing executive officer and joint head of operations group mr takanori nishiyama executive md head of compliance group managing executive officer  director age  compensation as of fiscal year  mizuho bank ltd key developments mizuho bank ltd announces executive changes jul   mizuho bank ltd changed the position of yasuhiko hashimoto from executive officer joint head of europe middle east and africa and general manager of europe structured finance department to executive officer joint head of europe middle east and africa effective as of july   mizuho bank ltd announces management changes jun   mizuho bank ltd changed the position of yasuyuki shibata from ex