みずほ type public company kk a mizuho financial group company industry financial services founded  headquarters otemachi chiyodaku tokyo japan key people nobuhide hayashi president  ceo revenue ¥ million nonconsolidated fy  net income ¥ million nonconsolidated fy  number of employees  nonconsolidated july  parent mizuho financial group subsidiaries mizuho securities uc card mizuho capital eurekahedge website wwwmizuhobankcom mizuho bank ginza branch mizuho bank ltd みずほ kabushikigaisha mizuho ginkō is the integrated retail and corporate banking unit of mizuho financial group tyo nysemfg one of the largest financial services companies in japan with total assets of approximately  trillion in  mizuho is one of the three socalled japanese megabanks along with mitsubishi ufj financial group and sumitomo mitsui financial group mizuho bank provides financial products and services to a wide range of clients including individuals small and mediumsized enterprises large corporations financial institutions and public sector entities its headquarters office building is located in the otemachi district of chiyoda tokyo mizuho bank has over  branches and offices in japan and in thirtysix other countries and regions and is the only bank to have branches in every prefecture in japan the name “mizuho” is an archaic japanese term meaning “golden ears of rice” and was used in the classical text nihon shoki to describe japan contents  history  services  botched trading scandal of   see also  references  external links historyedit announced in  mizuho financial group was established on april   by the merger of daiichi kangyo bank fuji bank and the industrial bank of japan all three predecessors were major financial institutions in their own right and had served as cornerstones of major zaibatsu prewar era and keiretsu postwar era in april  mizuho corporate bank and mizuho bank were established as two core banking subsidiaries of mizuho financial group through a split and merger process reorganizing the three legacy banks it was the first financial holding company structure created among major japanese banks mizuho corporate bank focused on large corporations financial institutions and public sector entities in japan and overseas mizuho bank focused on individuals and small and mediumsized companies in japan mizuho corporate bank engaged in steady expansion overseas opening twenty overseas offices between  and  particularly in china as well as in the americas europe and middle east in  mizuho corporate bank became the first japanese bank to obtain financial holding company status in the us and mizuho financial group listed its adrs on the new york stock exchange the two banks were initially consolidated under a holding company mizuho holdings on october   they were transferred to a new holding vehicle mizuho financial group on july   a merger between the former mizuho bank and the former mizuho corporate bank took place and the institution was named mizuho bank servicesedit current accounts cash cards for use in japan only international cash cards international money transfers credit cards saving accounts loans internet banking website all services including internet banking and the main website are in japanese only some branches hire englishspeaking employees all services except for international cash cards credit cards and international money transfers are limited within the territory of japan restrictions on foreign nationals apply particularly loans are available only for japanese nationals and permanent residents of japan holding permanent employmentcitation needed botched trading scandal of edit on thursday december   shares of recruitment firm jcom debuted at  japanese yen ¥  on the tokyo stock exchange the tse an inexperienced trader at mizuho intending to sell one share at ¥ instead sent an order at  am to the tse to sell  shares of jcom at ¥ each essentially attempting to sell  billion worth of stock for only  in addition the size of mizuhos sell order was  times the total number of jcom shares see alsoedit mizuho financial group mizuho corporate bank referencesedit  httpwwwmizuhobankcomcompanyreleasecbindexhtml  httpwwwmizuhobankcomcompanyreleasecbpdfnewspdf  httpwwwmizuhofgcojpenglishcompanyinfopdfreleaseengpdf  httpwwwmizuhofgcojpenglishreleasereleaseenghtml  operational risk  regulation  welcome to operational risk  regulation risknet external linksedit mizuho bank in japanese mizuho bank mizuho financial group the japan times – tse wont let mizuho duck jcom fiasco december   risknet – blame spreads over mizuho trading error december   msnbccom – botched stock trade costs japan firm m – december   risknet – mizuho securities loses m in trading error january   tokyo stock exchange – board report – april  the japan times – tse to blame for trading error court – december   the japan times – mizuho plans to appeal jcom ruling december   risknet – search mizuho trading error v t e mizuho financial group corporate mizuho corporate bank mizuho securities shinko securities retail mizuho bank mizuho investors securities uc card mizuho capital asset  wealth management mizuho trust  banking mizuho private wealth management trust  custody services bank mham diam strategy affiliates mizuho research institute mizuho information  research institute mizuho financial strategy historical components daiichi kangyo bank fuji bank industrial bank of japan ceo yasuhiro sato stock symbols tyo  ose  nyse mfg retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlemizuhobankoldid categories banks of japanfinancial services companies based in tokyojapanese brandsmizuho financial grouphidden categories use mdy dates from may pages using deprecated image syntaxpages using infobox company with unsupported parametersarticles containing japaneselanguage textall articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from november articles with japaneselanguage external links navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkc